{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1768945-83cd-4552-8f19-bf24e4ea3da5","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options:**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Common examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain contoso.onmicrosoft.com --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# No auth (add JWT Bearer manually)\ndotnet new webapi\n```\n\n**If you want JWT Bearer without Azure AD**, create with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually — this gives you full control over token validation.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"be466ec4-bf0d-4a2b-a899-99f000999b2b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general question about web API project templates and authentication options. This isn't a coding task - it's a knowledge question. I can answer this directly without needing to use any tools.\n\nActually, let me check if there's any context in the current working directory that might be relevant.","outputTokens":345,"requestId":"280C:18AE3E:11AF43:174016:69FFD72D"},"id":"b471e2e2-4538-413f-a30a-88002303002f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:14.819Z","parentId":"aa2ba6fe-e251-4675-8182-ee3f032bae3c"}
